//Some Validation classes on angular form
ng-untouched            <div *ngIf="firstName.invalid" && "firstname.dirty" class="alert alert-danger">                                  
ng-touched                         First Name is required
--------                 <div>
ng-pristine
ng-dirty
--------
ng-valid
ng-invalid
===================
//Disabling submit button
<button [disabled]="form.invalid">Ok</button>
=============================
:host==> By using this selector we can apply styles to host elements residing in parent component.
:host-context==> Works same as :host but based on some given condition.
/deep/==> Forces styles in its own component and all child components.
